1
00:00:00,800 --> 00:00:03,613
In the desert, they say a falcon always returns...

2
00:00:03,663 --> 00:00:06,477
to the hand that never stopped believing.

3
00:00:06,527 --> 00:00:09,340
For one old man, that hand has waited a very long time.

4
00:00:11,500 --> 00:00:13,200
Tonight, the falcon flies.

5
00:00:16,500 --> 00:00:21,140
Last time, we predicted Brazil would beat Haiti — and a supermarket worker stole the night.

6
00:00:21,190 --> 00:00:25,830
Tonight, a wounded host... against a silent machine.

7
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:30,870
Welcome back to WorldCup twenty-six Legends, episode nine. Qatar versus Switzerland.

8
00:00:30,920 --> 00:00:34,790
The desert fox against the alpine eagle.

9
00:00:37,500 --> 00:00:44,270
And stay with me — because in the seventy-eighth minute of our story, one free kick freezes an entire nation.

10
00:00:46,500 --> 00:00:51,440
First, the wound. Twenty twenty-two. Qatar hosts the World Cup...

11
00:00:51,490 --> 00:00:56,430
and loses every single match. The worst host performance in history.

12
00:00:57,000 --> 00:01:02,395
Four years carrying that shame.

13
00:01:02,445 --> 00:01:07,840
But the world forgot something: Qatar are the back-to-back kings of Asia — champions in twenty nineteen, and again in twenty twenty-three.

14
00:01:08,500 --> 00:01:12,015
Their conductor, Akram Afif, was the best player on the continent.

15
00:01:12,065 --> 00:01:15,580
This is no minnow. This is a wounded champion.

16
00:01:18,500 --> 00:01:21,453
And Switzerland? The quietest machine in football.

17
00:01:21,503 --> 00:01:24,457
At the last Euros, they knocked out world champions France...

18
00:01:24,507 --> 00:01:27,460
and broke a nation on penalties.

19
00:01:29,500 --> 00:01:31,865
Tonight, one of them needs only a point to survive.

20
00:01:31,915 --> 00:01:34,280
The other has nothing left to lose.

21
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:41,110
And nothing to lose is the most dangerous thing in all of sport.

22
00:01:44,500 --> 00:01:48,160
Meet the desert fox. Qatar — technical, patient, fearless.

23
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:55,093
Akram Afif, the magician who finds space that should not exist.

24
00:01:55,143 --> 00:01:59,237
Almoez Ali, the record-breaking striker.

25
00:01:59,287 --> 00:02:03,380
And Hassan Al-Haydos, the veteran captain... playing his very last World Cup match.

26
00:02:06,500 --> 00:02:09,380
Patience. Precision. And absolutely no fear.

27
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:17,595
But the alpine eagle does not panic.

28
00:02:17,645 --> 00:02:21,240
Switzerland reach the knockout rounds again and again — built like a Swiss watch.

29
00:02:23,500 --> 00:02:28,140
Granit Xhaka, the general who runs the tempo. Manuel Akanji, elegance in defense.

30
00:02:28,190 --> 00:02:32,830
And Dan Ndoye — electric feet on the right wing.

31
00:02:33,500 --> 00:02:37,460
Breel Embolo waits for one chance. Young Ardon Jashari drives the engine.

32
00:02:37,510 --> 00:02:41,470
They do not dazzle. They just... win.

33
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:46,270
One mistake tonight ends a World Cup.

34
00:02:49,500 --> 00:02:53,420
And the duel inside the match: Afif against Xhaka. The artist against the architect.

35
00:02:53,470 --> 00:02:57,390
Imagination... against order.

36
00:03:00,500 --> 00:03:03,495
Our prediction — built on the wound of twenty twenty-two, and on Swiss steel.

37
00:03:03,545 --> 00:03:06,540
Watch closely.

38
00:03:08,500 --> 00:03:11,123
Thirty-fourth minute.

39
00:03:11,173 --> 00:03:13,797
Afif splits the defense — Almoez Ali, one-on-one — but drags it wide!

40
00:03:13,847 --> 00:03:16,470
The golden chance... gone.

41
00:03:17,900 --> 00:03:21,025
Fifty-second minute. Switzerland strike like a watch.

42
00:03:21,075 --> 00:03:24,200
Ndoye beats his man, cuts it back —

43
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:31,940
Embolo! A thumping header! One-nil Switzerland. Swiss precision, Swiss result.

44
00:03:31,990 --> 00:03:36,930
But here it comes... the seventy-eighth minute.

45
00:03:38,500 --> 00:03:41,260
Afif stands over the free kick. Twenty-two yards.

46
00:03:41,310 --> 00:03:44,070
The whole desert holds its breath —

47
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:48,305
He curls it over the wall — SOMMER! Fingertips! Onto the bar!

48
00:03:48,355 --> 00:03:51,660
The human wall denies the magician!

49
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:57,820
Full time: one-nil Switzerland. The eagle advances.

50
00:03:57,870 --> 00:04:02,690
But Qatar walks off to an ovation — twenty twenty-two was a beginning, not an ending.

51
00:04:03,500 --> 00:04:06,625
Do you agree? Comment EAGLE if Switzerland go far this summer.

52
00:04:06,675 --> 00:04:09,800
Comment FALCON if Qatar shocks the group.

53
00:04:12,500 --> 00:04:17,085
And the old man with the falcon? Legend number nine: the Falconer of the Desert.

54
00:04:17,135 --> 00:04:21,720
He believed in Qatar... long before they had a stadium at all.

55
00:04:26,500 --> 00:04:29,400
Tonight, his falcon flew. Collect him inside the game.

56
00:04:32,500 --> 00:04:35,740
Which brings us to YOU.

57
00:04:35,790 --> 00:04:39,030
At WorldCup twenty-six dot world, pick three of the forty-eight nations — and every goal they score...

58
00:04:39,080 --> 00:04:42,320
scores for you.

59
00:04:43,900 --> 00:04:49,280
Free to play. Live leaderboard. Underdogs pay triple — like Qatar tonight.

60
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:53,495
Hit like — send this to the friend who wrote Qatar off.

61
00:04:53,545 --> 00:04:56,840
And subscribe: the legends are only beginning.

